---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Terms of Service — One Run Travel Packages">
  <Nav />
  <section style="padding:160px 48px 80px;max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="section-tag">Legal</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:32px;">Terms of <em>Service</em></h2>
    <div style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.9;color:rgba(243,239,232,0.65);">
      <p style="margin-bottom:24px;">Last updated: May 2026. By using the One Run platform and booking through our service, you agree to the following terms.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">1. Bookings</h3>
      <p>All bookings are made through our online platform at one-run.net. A booking is considered confirmed only after we have received full payment and sent you a written confirmation via email. We reserve the right to decline any booking at our discretion. It is your responsibility to provide accurate personal information, including full name as it appears on your identification document, date of birth, nationality, and valid contact details. Any errors in your booking information may result in the inability to participate in the race or use the accommodation, without a right to a refund.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">2. Race entry</h3>
      <p>Race entry is included in your package and is non-transferable. You must meet the minimum age requirement for your chosen race distance. Some races require a valid medical certificate confirming fitness to participate; it is your responsibility to obtain and submit this before the race deadline. You must collect your race bib in person during the official race expo or designated pickup window. Failure to do so will result in forfeiture of your race entry without refund. You agree to abide by the rules and regulations of the race organizer, including cut-off times and any decisions made by race officials.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">3. Payment</h3>
      <p>All prices are listed in euros (&euro;) and include applicable VAT. Payment must be made via bank transfer to our designated Alpha Bank account. Your booking is not confirmed until funds have cleared in our account. We are not responsible for any bank fees or currency conversion charges applied by your financial institution. In the event of an overpayment, we will refund the excess amount within 14 business days. Any promotional discounts or codes must be applied at the time of booking and cannot be applied retroactively.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">4. Liability</h3>
      <p>One Run acts as an intermediary between you (the runner) and third-party service providers including race organizers, hotels, and transfer operators. While we carefully select our partners, we are not liable for any acts, omissions, or negligence on the part of these third parties. Participation in any running event involves inherent risks including, but not limited to, personal injury, illness, and in extreme cases, death. By booking with us, you acknowledge these risks and agree that One Run, its directors, employees, and affiliates shall not be held liable for any injury, loss, or damage arising from your participation. We strongly recommend that you obtain comprehensive travel insurance covering race participation, medical expenses, and trip cancellation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</Base>
